org.forgerock.openam.sts.rest.operation.translate

Class CustomRestTokenProviderParametersImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openam.sts.rest.operation.translate.CustomRestTokenProviderParametersImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CustomRestTokenProviderParameters, RestTokenProviderParameters<org.forgerock.json.JsonValue>

    public class CustomRestTokenProviderParametersImpl
extends Object
implements CustomRestTokenProviderParameters
    This is an implementation of the RestTokenProviderParameters specific for custom RestTokenProvider implementations. It exposes the setter methods necessary to set the extra state added to the RestTokenProviderParameters interface to support custom providers.

      • getInputTokenType

        public TokenTypeId getInputTokenType()
        Description copied from interface: RestTokenProviderParameters
        Gets the type of the input token. Necessary to generate the authentication context class ref for a SAML2 assertion - in general, produced tokens may have to have a representation of how the subject encapsulated in the generated token was authenticated. Published sts instances allow for the specification of a Saml2JsonTokenAuthnContextMapper implementation which will generate this SAML2 authentication context class ref, a plug-in interface which takes the TokenTypeId as input. Published rest-sts instances which produce OpenIdConnect tokens have similar mapping implementations which produce the amr and acr claims.
        Specified by:
        getInputTokenType in interface RestTokenProviderParameters<org.forgerock.json.JsonValue>
        Returns:
        the type of the input token.

        Gets the json representation of the input token. Necessary to generate the authentication context class ref for a SAML2 assertion - in general, produced tokens may have to have a representation of how the subject encapsulated in the generated token was authenticated. Published sts instances allow for the specification of a Saml2JsonTokenAuthnContextMapper implementation which will generate this SAML2 authentication context class ref, a plug-in interface which takes the json representation of the token as input. Published rest-sts instances which produce OpenIdConnect tokens have similar mapping implementations which produce the amr and acr claims.
